article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 81, Long Beach St. 75
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- Aaron Thompson scored 10 of his 23 points in overtime to lead Cal State Fullerton to an 81-75 victory against Long Beach State on Thursday night. The first of Thompson's two 3-pointers in the extra session gave the Titans (11-10, 5-4 Big West) the lead for good, 69-66. He finished 8 for 8 from the floor. Gerard Anderson added 12 points for Fullerton. Bryce Webster had 11 points and 12 rebounds. Larry Anderson and Casper Ware scored 20 points each for Long Beach State (10-12, 4-5), and T.J. Robinson had 16 points and 13 rebounds.
